climbs.name: Unrepentant
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Great stone and continuously engaging movement make for an excellent route.  Make a cranky move past the first bolt.  Work up to some finger jams over a roof.  Continue up to another slightly overhanging finger crack and finish in a technical slot.

climbs.name: Sunsigns
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Scramble over acceptable stacked blocks.  Work up a creamy face on some large huecos.  Climb the overhanging right facing corner to the anchors.

climbs.name: Snake Eyes
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Climb a brown slab to blocks to a tan bulge.  Crank over the bulge and continue on good stone.  Finish on a long technical steep face.

climbs.name: Jump Street
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Layback off the ground over a boulder and move up to a steep brown face that is a little easier than it looks.

climbs.name: GoDoG
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Scramble up to the base of a bulge.  Pull over a bulge and work up to the steep overhanging corner guarding the anchors.

climbs.name: Get Over It
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Scramble up blocky, scruffy terrain to an obvious weakness in the roof band and pull the roof.  Climb heavily featured tan rock and follow the corner system to the anchors.

climbs.name: Feeding Frenzy
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Scramble up the base of large Juniper tree.  Follow a fun and challenging corner system in mostly tan rock to the anchors. Steep and pumpy.

climbs.name: Devil’s Tool
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Start on fractured but surprisingly good stone. Work up to an obvious undercling and lieback around a huge flake.
